{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "EquilibriumConstants",
        "description": "Aggregated equilibrium constants for ISORROPIA II. Composes 27 EqConst sub-components (r1...r27) from Table 2 of Fountoukis and Nenes (2007). Each ri.logK_eq(T) = logK0_i + H_i*(T0/T-1) + C_i*(1+ln(T0/T)-T0/T). A single T is broadcast to all subsystems via coupling equations. Migrated from Aerosol.jl@c8c640bb src/isorropia/equilibria.jl:22 (esm-y4v).",
        "tags": [
            "aerosol",
            "isorropia",
            "equilibrium",
            "thermodynamics",
            "inorganic-aerosol",
            "fountoukis-nenes-2007"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-21T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "Aerosol.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (esm-y4v)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Fountoukis, C. and Nenes, A. (2007). ISORROPIA II: a computationally efficient thermodynamic equilibrium model for K+-Ca2+-Mg2+-NH4+-Na+-SO42--NO3--Cl--H2O aerosols. Atmospheric Chemistry and Physics, 7(17), 4639-4659. https://doi.org/10.5194/acp-7-4639-2007. Equation 5 and Table 2."
            }
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "EquilibriumConstants": {
            "reference": {
                "citation": "Fountoukis, C. and Nenes, A. (2007). ISORROPIA II. Atmospheric Chemistry and Physics, 7(17), 4639-4659. https://doi.org/10.5194/acp-7-4639-2007. Table 2 (equilibrium constants r1-r27).",
                "notes": "source_ref: Aerosol.jl@c8c640bb636b22f2425460e9ed5cba50793bfee1:src/isorropia/equilibria.jl:22\n\nUpstream `EquilibriumConstants` is an MTK `@component` that instantiates 27 named `EqConst` subsystems (r1...r27) parameterized by Table 2 of Fountoukis & Nenes (2007). It declares a single `@variables` entry `T(t)` and 27 coupling equations `ri.T ~ T` broadcasting temperature to each sub-component. It also declares 27 unit-conversion @constants (k1_unit...k25_unit, k1b_unit, k2b_unit, all value=1) for the physical units of each K_i = exp(ri.logK_eq); migrated as top-level parameters with default=1.\n\nESM subsystem-composition pattern (ESS spec §4.7): 27 inline EqConst subsystems. Each subsystem T is re-typed from `parameter` (standalone) to `state` (composed) because the parent coupling equation `EquilibriumConstants.r{i}.T ~ T` governs it. Top-level equations use the full model-qualified path (EquilibriumConstants.r{i}.T) following the SulfateFormation precedent. logK0, H_coeff, C_coeff, T0 remain `parameter`; logK_eq is `observed` via Eq. 5.\n\nTolerance (rel=1e-8): purely algebraic observed system, matching eq_const.esm. identity_at_T0 verifies all 27 logK_eq=logK0 at T=T0. cold/warm tests spot-check r1 (H<0,C=0), r4 (H<0,C>0), r8 (H>0,C=0) at 250K and 310K."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1e-08
            },
            "variables": {
                "T": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 298.15,
                    "description": "Temperature. Broadcast to all 27 EqConst subsystems via coupling equations EquilibriumConstants.ri.T ~ T (i=1..27)."
                },
                "k1_unit": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "mol^3/kg^3",
                    "default": 1.0,
                    "description": "Unit conversion factor for r1: K_r1 = exp(r1.logK_eq) [mol^3/kg^3]. Upstream MTK @constants value=1."
                },
                "k2_unit": {
